{"parse":{"title":"9 Circles","pageid":42135413,"revid":853032517,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>9 Circles</b></i> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Play_(theatre)\" title=\"Play (theatre)\">play</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Bill_Cain\" title=\"Bill Cain\">Bill Cain</a> based on the military career and subsequent civilian trial of murderer <a href=\"/wiki/Steven_Dale_Green\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Steven Dale Green\">Steven Dale Green</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-AmericaMagazine9Circles_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-AmericaMagazine9Circles-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-DenverPost2012-01-19_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DenverPost2012-01-19-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ChicagoNow2013-09-07_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ChicagoNow2013-09-07-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ToonariPost2013-03-20_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ToonariPost2013-03-20-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-MDTheatreGuide2013-02-13_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MDTheatreGuide2013-02-13-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-DCTheatreScene2013-02-13_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DCTheatreScene2013-02-13-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Westword_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Westword-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Boston_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Boston-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Wapo2013-02-18_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wapo2013-02-18-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Nytimes2017-02-17_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Nytimes2017-02-17-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-TimeSquare2017-03-17_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-TimeSquare2017-03-17-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Cain is a <a href=\"/wiki/Jesuit_priest\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jesuit priest\">Jesuit priest</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-AmericaMagazine9Circles_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-AmericaMagazine9Circles-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The play's title refers to <a href=\"/wiki/Dante_Alighieri\" title=\"Dante Alighieri\">Dante Alighieri</a>'s <a href=\"/wiki/Inferno_(Dante)\" title=\"Inferno (Dante)\">Inferno</a>\u2014in which Dante navigates a descent into the \"nine circles of hell\". In Cain's play, Green passes through his discharge from the Army and various judicial and administrative procedures, roughly paralleling the nine circles of Dante's <i>Inferno</i>.  Cain structured the play so other cast members would return to play multiple characters, at each different circle.\n</p><p>The play won praise for being nuanced, and not taking the easy path of demonizing the protagonist.<sup id=\"cite_ref-AmericaMagazine9Circles_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-AmericaMagazine9Circles-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-DenverPost2012-01-19_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DenverPost2012-01-19-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ChicagoNow2013-09-07_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ChicagoNow2013-09-07-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ToonariPost2013-03-20_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ToonariPost2013-03-20-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-MDTheatreGuide2013-02-13_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MDTheatreGuide2013-02-13-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-DCTheatreScene2013-02-13_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DCTheatreScene2013-02-13-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Westword_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Westword-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Boston_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Boston-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Wapo2013-02-18_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wapo2013-02-18-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Nytimes2017-02-17_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Nytimes2017-02-17-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-TimeSquare2017-03-17_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-TimeSquare2017-03-17-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>  However, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chris_Jones_(reviewer)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Chris Jones (reviewer) (page does not exist)\">Chris Jones</a>, reviewing a <a href=\"/wiki/Chicago\" title=\"Chicago\">Chicago</a> production of the play, reported that audience members concluded the play meant to imply that Green, who was originally from <a href=\"/wiki/Midland,_Texas\" title=\"Midland, Texas\">Midland, Texas</a>, which had been <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_President\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"United States President\">United States President</a> <a href=\"/wiki/George_W._Bush\" title=\"George W. Bush\">George W. Bush</a>'s primary home, had the assistance of the President himself in clearing his entry into the Army in spite of his criminal record.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The play is receiving its Texas premiere in San Antonio, Texas with The Surround Project's production in June 2017.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The script won the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Steinberg_Award&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Steinberg Award (page does not exist)\">Steinberg Award</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>  Cain is the only playwright to have two plays win this award two years in a row.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=9_Circles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-AmericaMagazine9Circles-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-AmericaMagazine9Circles_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-AmericaMagazine9Circles_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-AmericaMagazine9Circles_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">John Coleman (2010-11-09). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://americamagazine.org/content/all-things/9-circles\">\"9 Circles\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/America_(Jesuit_magazine)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"America (Jesuit magazine)\">America</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140307030217/http://americamagazine.org/content/all-things/9-circles\">Archived</a> from the original on 2014-03-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>Jesuit playwright Bill Cain S.J., has penned a new and searingly powerful play. Just a year after his earlier successful play about the gun powder plot, Equivocation (see my review), Cain portrays in his new play, 9 Circles, a character, Daniel Reeves, as a disturbed 19-year-old snarled in the web of war. Cain's drama mirrors, through a fictional adaptation, the 2006 Iraq slayings and, subsequent, gang rape of a 14-year-old girl by United States troops. Like the real life Pvt. Steven Dale Green who, partially, serves as the prototype for Cain's Reeves and now awaits life prison without parole for his war crime, the fictional Reeves displays an 'anti-social personality disorder'.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=9+Circles&amp;rft.date=2010-11-09&amp;rft.au=John+Coleman&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Famericamagazine.org%2Fcontent%2Fall-things%2F9-circles&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ChicagoTribune2013-09-18_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\"><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chris_Jones_(reviewer)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Chris Jones (reviewer) (page does not exist)\">Chris Jones</a> (2013-09-18). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-09-18/entertainment/ct-ent-0919-circles-review-20130918_1_war-zone-trouble-woyzeck\">\"Looking for trouble in a war zone in '9 Circles<span style=\"padding-right:0.2em;\">'</span>\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Chicago_Tribune\" title=\"Chicago Tribune\">Chicago Tribune</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140306180439/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-09-18/entertainment/ct-ent-0919-circles-review-20130918_1_war-zone-trouble-woyzeck\">Archived</a> from the original on 2014-03-06<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>Or maybe that should be what a man can do to a war. \"9 Circles\" revolves around a central character, Private Daniel Reeves (Andrew Goetten), who already has been in plenty of trouble before he walks into the office of a recruiting officer looking for soldiers to go to Iraq. Cain's point, surely, is that Daniel, who goes on to commit horrible crimes that appall even the judicial system set up to process and try him, is precisely the wrong kind of man to be allowed to carry military-grade weaponry. The stresses of war, the play argues, could send anyone over the edge. When starting with a guy wound tight enough to burst his own blood-vessels, the smart leader would anticipate trouble.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Looking+for+trouble+in+a+war+zone+in+%279+Circles%27&amp;rft.date=2013-09-18&amp;rft.au=Chris+Jones&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farticles.chicagotribune.com%2F2013-09-18%2Fentertainment%2Fct-ent-0919-circles-review-20130918_1_war-zone-trouble-woyzeck&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-DenverPost2012-01-19-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-DenverPost2012-01-19_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-DenverPost2012-01-19_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Terry Frei (2012-01-19). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.denverpost.com/ci_19770102\">\"Theater review: Curious' \"9 Circles\" questions U.S. involvement in Iraq\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Denver_Post\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Denver Post\">Denver Post</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140307031312/http://www.denverpost.com/ci_19770102\">Archived</a> from the original on 2014-03-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>\"9 Circles\" is based on the infamous case of former 101st Airborne Division Pfc. Steven Dale Green, convicted in a federal court in 2009 of raping and killing an Iraqi 14-year-old girl and murdering her family. (Green's sentence, life in prison, was different than that of Reeves in the play.)</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Theater+review%3A+Curious%27+%229+Circles%22+questions+U.S.+involvement+in+Iraq&amp;rft.date=2012-01-19&amp;rft.au=Terry+Frei&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.denverpost.com%2Fci_19770102&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ChicagoNow2013-09-07-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ChicagoNow2013-09-07_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ChicagoNow2013-09-07_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Katy Walsh (2013-09-07). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chicagonow.com/the-fourth-walsh/2013/09/9-circles-sideshow-theatre-must-be-seen/\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">\"</span>9 Circles\" (Sideshow Theatre): Must Be Seen\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Chicago_Now\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Chicago Now\">Chicago Now</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140307031307/http://www.chicagonow.com/the-fourth-walsh/2013/09/9-circles-sideshow-theatre-must-be-seen/\">Archived</a> from the original on 2014-03-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>Playwright Bill Cain\u2019s story is set in 2006 Iraq but it could as easily be 2013 Syria.  The play\u2019s underlying questions of \u2018what is the USA doing? And why?\u2019 are timely to today\u2019s government debates.  Cain plots a soldier\u2019s persecution for horrific war crimes as the 9 circles of Dante\u2019s \u201cInferno.\u201d  A troubled nineteen year old is recruited by the military.  His stint is marred by extracurricular war activities.  Now, he is the focal point for the rage of the nationS.  He is *the* enemy, both foreign and domestic.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%229+Circles%22+%28Sideshow+Theatre%29%3A+Must+Be+Seen&amp;rft.date=2013-09-07&amp;rft.au=Katy+Walsh&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagonow.com%2Fthe-fourth-walsh%2F2013%2F09%2F9-circles-sideshow-theatre-must-be-seen%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ToonariPost2013-03-20-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ToonariPost2013-03-20_5-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ToonariPost2013-03-20_5-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Jason Loch (2013-03-20). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.toonaripost.com/2013/03/life-style/9-circles-by-bill-cain-review/\">\"9 Circles by Bill Cain Review\"</a>. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Toonari_Post&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Toonari Post (page does not exist)\">Toonari Post</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140307031301/http://www.toonaripost.com/2013/03/life-style/9-circles-by-bill-cain-review/\">Archived</a> from the original on 2014-03-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>From that point on, Reeves is on a downward spiral. He ends up in jail, accused of raping a 14-year old Iraqi girl and killing her along with her entire family. As he waits for a judge to decide his fate, he encounters various people who allegedly want to help him, from an enigmatic army lawyer (William Bolz) to a pastor with a penchant for internet porn (Whitney Derendinger). In a way, they play the role of Virgil to Reeves\u2019 Dante, and each one of them helps guide Reeves along the path to self-discovery.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=9+Circles+by+Bill+Cain+Review&amp;rft.date=2013-03-20&amp;rft.au=Jason+Loch&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.toonaripost.com%2F2013%2F03%2Flife-style%2F9-circles-by-bill-cain-review%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-MDTheatreGuide2013-02-13-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-MDTheatreGuide2013-02-13_6-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-MDTheatreGuide2013-02-13_6-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Roger Catlin (2013-02-13). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mdtheatreguide.com/2013/02/theatre-review-9-circles-at-forum-theatre\">\"Theatre Review: '9 Circles' at Forum Theatre\"</a>. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Maryland_Theatre_Guide&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Maryland Theatre Guide (page does not exist)\">Maryland Theatre Guide</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20130217032322/http://www.mdtheatreguide.com/2013/02/theatre-review-9-circles-at-forum-theatre\">Archived</a> from the original on 2013-02-17<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>9 Circles is inspired by an actual case, that of former 101st Airborne Division Pfc. Steven Dale Green, convicted in federal court in 2009 for raping and killing a 14-year-old Iraqi girl and murdering her family.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Theatre+Review%3A+%E2%80%999+Circles%E2%80%99+at+Forum+Theatre&amp;rft.date=2013-02-13&amp;rft.au=Roger+Catlin&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdtheatreguide.com%2F2013%2F02%2Ftheatre-review-9-circles-at-forum-theatre&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-DCTheatreScene2013-02-13-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-DCTheatreScene2013-02-13_7-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-DCTheatreScene2013-02-13_7-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Ben Demers (2013-02-13). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dctheatrescene.com/2013/02/14/9-circles/\">\"9 Circles\"</a>. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=DC_Theatre_Scene&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"DC Theatre Scene (page does not exist)\">DC Theatre Scene</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140307031630/http://dctheatrescene.com/2013/02/14/9-circles/\">Archived</a> from the original on 2014-03-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>Private Daniel Edward Reeves, played by the astonishing Julian Elijah Martinez, stands accused of heinous crimes in Iraq. Reeves is trapped onstage in a concentric limbo of military tribunals, therapy sessions, and jail cells, dressed in stark white scenery by Klyph Stanford and lit in harsh tones by Dan Covey.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=9+Circles&amp;rft.date=2013-02-13&amp;rft.au=Ben+Demers&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fdctheatrescene.com%2F2013%2F02%2F14%2F9-circles%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Westword-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Westword_8-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Westword_8-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Juliet Whitman (2012-01-19). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.westword.com/2012-01-19/culture/9-circles-mahmudiyah-killings-play/full/\">\"Based on Iraq War atrocities, 9 Circles is clear-eyed and tightly written\"</a>. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Denver_Westword_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Denver Westword Arts (page does not exist)\">Denver Westword Arts</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140307031610/http://www.westword.com/2012-01-19/culture/9-circles-mahmudiyah-killings-play/full/\">Archived</a> from the original on 2014-03-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>I was ambivalent about seeing Curious Theatre's regional premiere of Bill Cain's 9 Circles, whose plot tracks very closely with Green's known actions and experiences.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Based+on+Iraq+War+atrocities%2C+9+Circles+is+clear-eyed+and+tightly+written&amp;rft.date=2012-01-19&amp;rft.au=Juliet+Whitman&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.westword.com%2F2012-01-19%2Fculture%2F9-circles-mahmudiyah-killings-play%2Ffull%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Boston-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Boston_9-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Boston_9-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://timeoutboston.com/arts-culture/theater/90753/review-9-circles\">\"Review: 9 Circles\"</a>. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Time_Out_Boston&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Time Out Boston (page does not exist)\">Time Out Boston</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20140307035208/http://timeoutboston.com/arts-culture/theater/90753/review-9-circles\">Archived</a> from the original on 2014-03-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-03-06</span></span>. <q>With all the action of the show staged on a claustrophobic circular plinth, 9 Circles takes us through a wretched year in the life of an Iraq War vet. We follow Private Daniel Reeves through a series of holding cells and psychiatrists\u2019 offices, as he is indicted for a war crime he allegedly committed while in Iraq. Amanda Collins and Will McGarrahan play a slew of lawyers, military personnel and other authority figures who come to vie for possession of Reeves\u2019s soul.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Review%3A+9+Circles&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ftimeoutboston.com%2Farts-culture%2Ftheater%2F90753%2Freview-9-circles&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Wapo2013-02-18-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Wapo2013-02-18_10-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Wapo2013-02-18_10-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Celia Wren (2013-02-18). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/theater_dance/9-circles-offers-a-thoughtful-but-unemotional-descent-into-cruelty-of-war/2013/02/15/0463cbd2-7794-11e2-8f84-3e4b513b1a13_story.html\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">'</span>9 Circles' offers a thoughtful but unemotional descent into cruelty of war\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Washington_Post\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Washington Post\">Washington Post</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-02-13</span></span>. <q>The intense tete-a-tetes \u2014 which offer occasional moments of humor \u2014 tease out provocative questions about war, justice, guilt and America\u2019s possible exploitation of its troops.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Washington+Post&amp;rft.atitle=%E2%80%989+Circles%E2%80%99+offers+a+thoughtful+but+unemotional+descent+into+cruelty+of+war&amp;rft.date=2013-02-18&amp;rft.au=Celia+Wren&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftheater_dance%2F9-circles-offers-a-thoughtful-but-unemotional-descent-into-cruelty-of-war%2F2013%2F02%2F15%2F0463cbd2-7794-11e2-8f84-3e4b513b1a13_story.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Nytimes2017-02-17-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Nytimes2017-02-17_11-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Nytimes2017-02-17_11-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Laura Collins-Hughes (2017-02-17). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/27/theater/9-circles-review.html\">\"Review: '9 Circles,' a Soldier's Story (and the Damage Done)\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Times\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York Times\">New York Times</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-02-13</span></span>. <q>In Bill Cain\u2019s \u201c9 Circles,\u201d a contemporary morality play inspired by Dante\u2019s \u201cThe Divine Comedy,\u201d the psychic damage of war does not belong to Reeves alone, and neither do the responsibilities of conscience.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Review%3A+%E2%80%989+Circles%2C%E2%80%99+a+Soldier%E2%80%99s+Story+%28and+the+Damage+Done%29&amp;rft.date=2017-02-17&amp;rft.au=Laura+Collins-Hughes&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2017%2F02%2F27%2Ftheater%2F9-circles-review.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-TimeSquare2017-03-17-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-TimeSquare2017-03-17_12-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-TimeSquare2017-03-17_12-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\">Suzanna Bowling (2017-03-17). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://t2conline.com/nine-circles-portrait-of-an-iraqi-killer/\">\"Nine Circles Portrait of an Iraqi Killer\"</a>. <i>Time Square Chronicles</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-02-12</span></span>. <q>War is psychologically damaging and like parking tickets or speeding tickets given out just to make their quota, recruters should not pad their numbers with psychologically unfit people and not expect criminal activity.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Time+Square+Chronicles&amp;rft.atitle=Nine+Circles+Portrait+of+an+Iraqi+Killer&amp;rft.date=2017-03-17&amp;rft.au=Suzanna+Bowling&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ft2conline.com%2Fnine-circles-portrait-of-an-iraqi-killer%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-13\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thesurroundproject.com\">\"(no title)\"</a>. <i>www.thesurroundproject.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-05-12</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.thesurroundproject.com&amp;rft.atitle=%28no+title%29&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurroundproject.com&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A9+Circles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-14\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-14\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.greenbaypressgazette.com/story/news/local/door-co/entertainment/2018/02/12/third-avenue-playhouse-opens-winter-play-reading-festival/331652002/\">Third Avenue Playhouse opens Winter Play Reading Festival</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2135\nCached time: 20180915175847\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.416 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.447 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 784/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 31309/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 468/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recurs